9cnw f1g87ej0 freluf8 f1yggaq6 f2i3chp f1151osp florpoh f35kzfz ftp9m57 f1e288vi fz62hnz fixvuys f1nmofwh fc1c6mv f18a2er7 fhvkrdl fhxnn68 f1oce4bo fvhlfan f7tc0t0 f1ngf1n2 ffrzq6x f1yjiq2m f1aqdgql f1huvaf f10ij78l f1k94sa4 fkmfumq f1jvzkyl f1eu24ob f1xbfc1f fmf0lwf f107dsy8 f3w566c f4648sl f13zpkng f7unjfp f8p1rz fzu6h1w f1i1bi6h f1smo7hi f1sk1xod f1kgogdq f1gjktkp ft608jz f19dd9cz fg3xr24 fhd155k f1b8gl2e fg4b9ou flb4lo fdicbfk fgwcyh1 f1jbds0d f1fb9uea f1stuka4 fcrtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>Short answer: <strong>Yes—apply</strong>, but treat it as a <strong>stretch</strong> role and tailor your materials to emphasize implementation leadership, hospital workflows, vendor coordination, and stakeholder management. You’ve been targeting implementation PM roles for a while, and this posting aligns with your direction (enterprise software/hospital network, customer-facing, cross‑functional leadership). Your Revenue Integrity + Cloudmed/FinThrive/Cerner context is relevant if we position it correctly.</p>
<p>Below is a quick fit check, the gaps, and exactly how to frame your resume and talking points to clear the bar.</p>
<hr>
<h2>Quick Fit Check</h2>
<p><strong>Strong signals you bring</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Healthcare enterprise context:</strong> Banner Health, multi-site operations, RI audits, charge workflows (Cloudmed, FinThrive, Craneware, Lawson, Spacetrax, Cerner exposure).</li>
<li><strong>Customer-facing + stakeholder management:</strong> You coordinate with QA, Coding, Charge Integrity, cath/IR, RAD-ONC—this is analogous to vendor ↔ client stakeholder work.</li>
<li><strong>Process/implementation mindset:</strong> You’ve been building a 2‑year optimization plan ahead of Cerner go‑live, designing test cases, mock dashboards, charge capture workflow improvements.</li>
<li><strong>Travel-ready &amp; remote-savvy:</strong> Comfortable with distributed teams and onsite coordination as needed.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Likely gaps to close</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Formal implementation PM years (5+)</strong>: Your title history is RI-focused vs. implementation PM. We’ll translate your project work into “implementation‑adjacent” outcomes and quantify scope.</li>
<li><strong>PMP “highly preferred”:</strong> You don’t have it yet. We’ll counter with structured methods (charters, RACI, RAID, critical path, change control) and hospital rollouts.</li>
<li><strong>Hardware installs exposure:</strong> You haven’t led hardware installs (surgical screens, laptops). We’ll bridge with your experience coordinating with Supply Chain/Lawson/Spacetrax, device/supply mappings, and propose an SME‑supported rollout model.</li>
<li><strong>Time zone note:</strong> Role prefers ET/CT. You’re in MT. Some companies are flexible; be ready to work ET hours.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Decision Framework (1–minute)</h2>
<ul>
<li>If you can show <strong>3–5 concrete projects</strong> where you led cross‑functional delivery with timelines, dependencies, and go‑live/benefit realization → <strong>Apply</strong>.</li>
<li>If you can’t produce those, but can present <strong>implementation‑adjacent</strong> outcomes (audit-to-correction workflows, charge capture remediation, multi‑department cutovers) with measurable impact → <strong>Apply, but as a stretch</strong>.</li>
<li>If you cannot adjust to ET hours or do 20–25% travel → <strong>Pass</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Given what I know about you, I recommend you <strong>apply as a stretch</strong> and let’s tailor materials to maximize relevance.</p>
<hr>
<h2>How to Position Your Experience (Resume &amp; Interview)</h2>
<h3>Core positioning statement (top of resume / LinkedIn)</h3>
<p><strong>Implementation‑focused Project Manager (Healthcare)</strong> driving multi‑site hospital software/process deployments across Revenue Integrity and charge capture. Leads cross‑functional stakeholders (RI, Coding, Cath/IR, RAD‑ONC, Supply Chain) to deliver accurate charging, CDM alignment, and audit remediation. Experienced with Cloudmed, FinThrive, Craneware CDM, Lawson, Spacetrax, and Cerner context. Strong at project governance (RAID, change control), training coordination, and go‑live support.</p>
<h3>Translate your experience into “Implementation” language</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>From:</strong> Post‑bill RI audits and charge corrections<br>
<strong>To:</strong> “Led phased rollout of charge remediation workflows across [X] facilities, coordinating Cloudmed findings → Coding/Charge Integrity actions, with change control and defect tracking; reduced missed charges by <strong>Y%</strong> within <strong>Z months</strong>.”</li>
<li><strong>From:</strong> Cloudmed/R1 algorithm review<br>
<strong>To:</strong> “Managed deployment of algorithm‑based detection rules (Cloudmed/R1) to improve charge completeness; facilitated UAT with SMEs; tracked false‑positive rates and tuned rule thresholds to achieve <strong>A% precision</strong>.”</li>
<li><strong>From:</strong> Supply chain mapping (Lawson/Spacetrax)<br>
<strong>To:</strong> “Coordinated device/supply mapping (Lawson/Spacetrax → CDM) with clinical SMEs; established cutover plan and issue triage for go‑live; resolved <strong>N</strong> critical defects within <strong>48 hours</strong>.”</li>
<li><strong>From:</strong> Collaboration limits in current role<br>
<strong>To:</strong> “Functioned as the point person across departments despite organizational constraints, establishing RACI and escalation paths to deliver on-time resolutions.”</li>
</ul>
<h3>Hardware angle (bridge statement)</h3>
<p>“While my core implementations are software/process, I’ve coordinated with Supply Chain and clinical engineering for device/supply readiness and can oversee hardware install workstreams by partnering with field engineers and site leads, using site readiness checklists, scheduling windows, and post‑install QA.”</p>
<hr>
<h2>Resume Bullet Examples (you can paste/edit)</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Led</strong> a multi‑site rollout of Cloudmed‑driven charge capture remediation across <strong>X hospitals</strong>, orchestrating Coding, Charge Integrity, and cath/IR SMEs; implemented RAID logs, weekly standups, and change control, achieving <strong>Y%</strong> reduction in missed/late charges within <strong>Z months</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Managed</strong> CDM alignment with Craneware and Lawson/Spacetrax supply mapping for IR/CATH and RAD‑ONC; developed a cutover plan and UAT scripts; achieved <strong>&lt;2%</strong> post‑go‑live defect rate.</li>
<li><strong>Directed</strong> end‑user readiness and training coordination for RI/QA workflow updates (SBO entry team, Coding, clinical departments); produced quick‑reference job aids and set up hypercare channels, reducing ticket resolution time by <strong>A%</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Implemented</strong> controls for ED fracture audits (e.g., CPT 25605 soft code + 0450 revenue code); standardized negative line handling in MS4; lifted first‑pass claim accuracy by <strong>B%</strong> in <strong>C months</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Partnered</strong> with QA to validate drug‑free program accuracy; performed NCCI/bundling checks and component ownership reviews, decreasing compliance risk and write‑offs by <strong>$D</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>(We’ll plug in your actual numbers—give me rough ranges and I’ll finalize.)</em></p>
<hr>
<h2>Interview Talking Points (align to the posting)</h2>
<p><strong>Leading large-scale enterprise implementation</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Walk through a <strong>multi‑site</strong> rollout you led end‑to‑end: charter → plan → dependencies (Coding/SBO/IT) → UAT → go‑live → hypercare → benefits realized.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Point person &amp; stakeholder management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Your cross‑functional coordination (RI, Coding, Cath/IR, RAD‑ONC, Supply Chain). Mention cadence: weekly steering, project standups, issue review.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Hardware installation oversight</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Outline your <strong>site readiness checklist</strong>: inventory validation, power/network checks, delivery windows, install sequencing, downtime plan, acceptance testing, and sign‑off. Emphasize you leverage field SMEs.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>End‑user training</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Your experience creating concise RI job aids and coordinating training sessions; how you measure adoption (tickets, error rates, accuracy).</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Healthcare/EMR context</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Banner (MS4 billing, Cerner charting, Cloudmed/FinThrive/Craneware/Lawson/Spacetrax), ED audit specifics, NCCI/bundling logic—demonstrates you speak hospital ops fluently.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>PMP preference</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>If asked, emphasize structured PM methods you use (RACI, WBS, critical path, risk scoring, change control). If you’re willing to pursue PMP within 6–9 months, say so.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Compensation &amp; Logistics</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>$65–$70/hr W2</strong> (~$135k–$146k/year at 2,080 hrs). This is within range of your $150k target, especially with OT or if rate is flexible.</li>
<li><strong>Travel 20–25%</strong>: You’re comfortable with this.</li>
<li><strong>Time zone</strong>: They prefer ET/CT. Offer to work ET hours from Mountain Time.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Smart Questions to Ask the Recruiter/Hiring Manager</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Scope &amp; success:</strong> “How many facilities/sites and what’s the target go‑live schedule? What are the top 3 success metrics?”</li>
<li><strong>Hardware ownership:</strong> “Who executes installs—internal field engineers or partner vendors? What’s the PM’s role in QA/acceptance?”</li>
<li><strong>Training plan:</strong> “Is there a standard curriculum or does the PM build it with SMEs? What tools do you use for LMS/tracking?”</li>
<li><strong>Governance:</strong> “Do you use a standard RAID/issue tracker, change control board, and risk scoring model?”</li>
<li><strong>Team structure:</strong> “What’s the SME bench (clinical, IT, revenue cycle)? Who is my counterpart at the customer?”</li>
<li><strong>Travel cadence:</strong> “Are trips clustered around readiness assessments, go‑lives, or executive workshops?”</li>
<li><strong>Renewals &amp; runway:</strong> “Is this a single implementation or a program of rollouts? What does success unlock after the first wave?”</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2>Cover Letter / Email Blurb (paste-ready)</h2>
<blockquote>
<p>I’m a healthcare implementation‑focused PM with deep Revenue Integrity and multi‑department hospital experience (Cloudmed, FinThrive, Craneware CDM, Lawson, Spacetrax, Cerner context). I’ve led multi‑site rollouts of charge capture and CDM alignment initiatives, partnering with Coding, Charge Integrity, Supply Chain, and clinical SMEs to deliver measurable improvements in first‑pass accuracy and charge completeness. I run structured delivery (RAID logs, change control, UAT/hypercare) and coordinate end‑user training and job aids to ensure adoption. While my implementations have been software/process‑heavy, I’m comfortable overseeing hardware install workstreams via site readiness checklists and SME field support. I’m available to work ET hours and travel 20–25% as needed. I’d love to discuss how I can drive your hospital system implementations to on‑time, on‑budget, high‑adoption outcomes.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2>Next Steps (I can do this for you)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Share your current resume (or bullets). I’ll <strong>rewrite and tailor</strong> it to this JD with quantified outcomes.</li>
<li>I’ll craft a <strong>1‑page project summary</strong> (“program sheet”) showcasing your best hospital rollouts and governance artifacts.</li>
<li>We can do a <strong>30‑minute mock screen</strong> focused on the hardware + training angles.</li>
</ul>
<p>Do you want me to tailor your resume and produce the project summary now? If you send me rough metrics (even ranges), I’ll fill them in and tighten the narrative for this application.</p>
