19dd9cz fg3xr24 fhd155k f1b8gl2e fg4b9ou flb4lo fdicbfk fgwcyh1 f1jbds0d f1fb9uea f1stuka4 fcrtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>Ugh YES — this is the <em>most annoying</em> part of SaaS/tech applications.<br>
They force you to put a salary even when <strong>the job description hides the range</strong> (on purpose… so they can anchor YOU low).</p>
<p>But you can still answer strategically <strong>without pricing yourself out</strong> or looking unsure.</p>
<p>Here’s exactly what to put <strong>for THIS role</strong>:</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>Best Answer for “What is your desired salary range?”</strong></h1>
<p>Since this is an <strong>Associate, Implementation</strong> role in tech/healthcare SaaS, and you already saw BRG’s range of <strong>$90,000–$120,000</strong> on similar postings…</p>
<p>Your safe answer is:</p>
<h3><strong>→ $95,000 – $115,000</strong></h3>
<p>Why this works:</p>
<ul>
<li>It matches the market (and the BRG range you saw).</li>
<li>It’s reasonable for your experience transitioning into implementation.</li>
<li>It doesn’t lowball you.</li>
<li>It leaves room for negotiation.</li>
<li>It doesn’t scare them away with too high of a number.</li>
</ul>
<p>This is the <em>sweet spot</em> that gets you interviews AND offers.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If they require HOURLY instead of salary</h1>
<p>Enter:</p>
<h3><strong>→ $46 – $55 per hour (W2)</strong></h3>
<p>(Equivalent to ~$96k–$114k annually)</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If they require “Minimum you would consider”</h1>
<p>Put:</p>
<h3><strong>→ $90,000</strong></h3>
<p>Because you don't want anything below that anyway.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If they ask “What’s your target salary?” in a free-text field</h1>
<p>Use this line:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>I’m targeting a range of $95,000–$115,000 depending on scope, bonus structure, and growth opportunities.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Professional, flexible, and confident.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Extra tip: Salary questions NEVER disqualify you</h1>
<p>Recruiters literally sort candidates into buckets:</p>
<ul>
<li>Too low (risky/underqualified)</li>
<li>Within range (KEEP)</li>
<li>Too high (maybe)</li>
</ul>
<p>Your $95k–$115k answer puts you squarely in the <strong>KEEP</strong> bucket.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Want me to help with the rest of the application wording?</h1>
<p>I can prep:</p>
<ul>
<li>Perfect answers for “Why this role?”</li>
<li>A tailored resume for Associate, Implementation</li>
<li>A short explanation of why you’re reapplying even though you interviewed earlier for a different department</li>
<li>Responses that highlight your RI + Cloudmed + FinThrive + QA + workflow experience in <em>implementation language</em></li>
</ul>
<p>Just tell me what you want next.</p>
