d f1fb9uea f1stuka4 fcrtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>Great question — and <strong>YES</strong>, if you choose an <strong>EST hub</strong>, most companies <em>expect you to work EST hours</em>, even if you live in Mountain Time.</p>
<p>But here’s the nuance you need to know so you choose wisely:</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>If you pick EST, what schedule will they expect?</strong></h1>
<p>Usually:</p>
<h3><strong>EST schedule: 9am–5pm EST</strong></h3>
<p>For you in Colorado (Mountain Time):</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>7am–3pm MT</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>So YES — you’ll start earlier but also <strong>get off work earlier</strong>.<br>
This is actually an advantage if you prefer early shifts.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Why companies ask for a “location preference” even though it’s remote</h1>
<p>For Implementation &amp; Consulting roles, it’s usually because:</p>
<h3>1. <strong>Your working hours must match your assigned region</strong></h3>
<p>If you pick:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>NYC, Boston, DC</strong> → They assume <strong>EST availability</strong></li>
<li><strong>Dallas, Chicago, Nashville</strong> → Usually <strong>CST</strong></li>
<li><strong>Phoenix, Salt Lake, Las Vegas</strong> → Usually <strong>MST/PST</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>2. <strong>Client meetings will follow that region’s timezone</strong></h3>
<p>If they map you to an EST client hub → You follow EST hours for calls.</p>
<h3>3. <strong>Travel assignments depend on region</strong></h3>
<p>Choosing a hub affects:</p>
<ul>
<li>Which clients you’re matched to</li>
<li>Where you may occasionally travel</li>
<li>Which implementation team you’re aligned with</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Should YOU choose EST?</h1>
<p>Ask yourself:</p>
<h3>✔️ Do you like starting early and finishing early?</h3>
<p>If YES → EST is perfect.</p>
<h3>✔️ Do you mind being on 7am calls?</h3>
<p>If you’re okay with that → choose EST.</p>
<h3>✔️ Do you want to appear more “flexible” to recruiters?</h3>
<p>Choosing EST usually expands your opportunities because many clients are East Coast.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Should you choose MST hubs instead?</h1>
<p>If you prefer a normal schedule, selected hubs like:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Phoenix, AZ</strong></li>
<li><strong>Salt Lake City, UT</strong></li>
<li><strong>Las Vegas, NV</strong></li>
<li><strong>Dallas, TX (CST)</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>These allow meetings in your natural time zone.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ My recommendation for YOU specifically</h1>
<p>Based on how you like:</p>
<ul>
<li>Getting things done early</li>
<li>Being free earlier in the day</li>
<li>Working remote without late-day meetings</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Best pick: Choose EST hubs.</strong></h3>
<p>You will:</p>
<ul>
<li>Start at <strong>7am MT</strong></li>
<li>Get off at <strong>3pm MT</strong></li>
<li>Avoid evening meetings</li>
<li>Look more flexible/appealing as a candidate</li>
<li>Fit better with many implementation teams that run on EST</li>
</ul>
<p>This is a <strong>strategic advantage</strong>, not a disadvantage.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Final recommendation (copy/paste selections)</h1>
<p>Select:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>New York, NY</strong></li>
<li><strong>Boston, MA</strong></li>
<li><strong>Washington, DC</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>And optionally:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Dallas, TX</strong> (central hub and widely used)</li>
<li><strong>Phoenix, AZ</strong> (closer to you in case they want region mapping)</li>
</ul>
<p>This gives you flexibility AND makes your profile stronger.</p>
<hr>
<p>If you want, I can also:</p>
<ul>
<li>Review all your answers before submitting</li>
<li>Help craft your “Why this role?” response</li>
<li>Polish your resume for Associate, Implementation</li>
</ul>
