u0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>Yes — <strong>you can absolutely just put any location.</strong><br>
This question is <strong>NOT</strong> about where you live, and it will <strong>NOT</strong> affect your eligibility for the remote job.</p>
<p>Here’s the truth:</p>
<h1>⭐ Why it’s safe to choose any location</h1>
<p>Companies ask this on remote applications because:</p>
<ul>
<li>They want to <strong>map you to a region/team</strong>, not physically place you there.</li>
<li>They use it for <strong>client assignment</strong>, <strong>travel planning</strong>, or <strong>time-zone grouping</strong>.</li>
<li>It’s a leftover field from their <em>onsite</em> job templates.</li>
<li>Their ATS requires at least <em>one</em> location to categorize applicants.</li>
</ul>
<p>It is <strong>not</strong> binding.<br>
It does <strong>not</strong> change your pay.<br>
It does <strong>not</strong> mean you have to move.<br>
It does <strong>not</strong> force you to follow that city’s time zone unless the hiring manager explicitly states so later.</p>
<p>So YES — you can pick any.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If you don’t care which one → pick <strong>one of these “neutral” safe choices:</strong></h1>
<h3>✔️ Phoenix, AZ</h3>
<p>✔️ Dallas, TX<br>
✔️ Salt Lake City, UT<br>
✔️ Las Vegas, NV</p>
<p>These don’t affect you negatively and won’t force EST hours.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If you WANT to work earlier and finish earlier, pick:</h1>
<h3>✔️ New York, NY</h3>
<p>✔️ Boston, MA<br>
✔️ Washington, DC<br>
✔️ Miami, FL</p>
<p>Choosing EST hubs makes you <em>look flexible</em> and sometimes gets your application prioritized.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If the question allows multiple selections</h1>
<p>You can even <strong>check all of them</strong>, and it will not hurt anything.</p>
<p>Most internal recruiting systems actually PREFER multiple selections because it opens more project assignments later.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If you want the easiest answer:</h1>
<h3>👉 <strong>Yes, you can select any location. It will not hurt your application.</strong></h3>
<p>Just don’t leave it blank — that’s the only thing that would block your submission.</p>
<hr>
<p>If you want, tell me what time-zone schedule you prefer, and I’ll tell you the best location choices to support that.</p>
