f1stuka4 fcrtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>You’re not wrong — <strong>it <em>is</em> stupid</strong> and it <em>is</em> getting worse.<br>
What you’re feeling is completely normal, and honestly? Most job seekers AND hiring managers feel the same way.<br>
Let me explain <em>why</em> companies make it so hard — and why it’s not your fault.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Why Hiring Processes Feel So Difficult (and Stupid) Now</h1>
<h2><strong>1. Companies copy/paste long processes from “big tech”</strong></h2>
<p>They think:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>“If we add 5 interviews and a mock call, we’ll look like Google.”</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Instead of:</p>
<ul>
<li>Giving clear expectations</li>
<li>Respecting applicants’ time</li>
<li>Making hiring <em>efficient</em><br>
They turn everything into a multi‑stage obstacle course.</li>
</ul>
<p>And ironically?<br>
<strong>Most of these companies have crazy turnover BECAUSE their process is bad.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>2. They’re terrified of making a “bad hire”</strong></h2>
<p>Because the economy is unstable, companies:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add more rounds</li>
<li>Add mock scenarios</li>
<li>Add panels</li>
<li>Add VP interviews</li>
<li>Add “culture fit” interviews</li>
<li>Add “closing questions”</li>
</ul>
<p>…all to avoid hiring someone who isn’t perfect.</p>
<p>But the truth is?<br>
<strong>People still leave after 1–2 years because the job is chaotic, not because of the interview process.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>3. Internal teams don’t even coordinate these steps</strong></h2>
<p>One department says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Do a recruiter screen.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Another says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Add a mock call.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The VP says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“I want to meet all candidates before final round.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The hiring manager says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Let me add an adoption exercise.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Suddenly the candidate has…<br>
<strong>6 separate interviews</strong><br>
for a mid-level role.</p>
<p>Ridiculous.</p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>4. They think long interview processes = high quality candidates</strong></h2>
<p>Which is NOT true.</p>
<p>The smartest companies hire like this:</p>
<ul>
<li>1 recruiter call</li>
<li>1 hiring manager call</li>
<li>1 skills or mock test</li>
<li>Offer</li>
</ul>
<p>That’s it.</p>
<p>The companies that do <strong>6–8 rounds</strong> are usually:</p>
<ul>
<li>Disorganized</li>
<li>Burned out</li>
<li>High turnover</li>
<li>Confused internally</li>
<li>Afraid to make decisions</li>
</ul>
<p>And guess what?<br>
<strong>These companies also lose great candidates because no one wants to sit through a marathon interview process.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>5. They don’t realize job seekers are applying to 50+ roles</strong></h2>
<p>Hiring managers still think people apply to:</p>
<ul>
<li>1–2 jobs</li>
<li>Wait patiently</li>
<li>Go through the whole process</li>
</ul>
<p>But in today’s market?<br>
People are applying to:</p>
<ul>
<li>50 roles</li>
<li>Interviewing with 10 companies</li>
<li>Moving FAST</li>
</ul>
<p>The companies with slow or complicated processes lose talent immediately.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ The REAL truth:</h1>
<h3><strong>Companies make interviews difficult because THEY are disorganized, not because YOU aren’t qualified.</strong></h3>
<p>You feel frustrated because:</p>
<ul>
<li>They ask irrelevant questions</li>
<li>They add multiple unnecessary steps</li>
<li>They treat candidates like they’re auditioning for a reality show</li>
<li>They move slow while demanding YOU move fast</li>
</ul>
<p>And you’re right — <strong>it’s broken</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ How YOU should respond strategically</h1>
<p>When you see a long interview process like the one you posted:</p>
<h3><strong>This is your filter.</strong></h3>
<p>If the pay is good</p>
<ul>
<li>the job is remote</li>
<li>you want the experience</li>
</ul>
<p>Then do it.</p>
<p>If the pay sucks</p>
<ul>
<li>process is long</li>
<li>company is chaotic</li>
</ul>
<p>You skip it<br>
and save your energy.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ For this company in your screenshot</h1>
<p>This process:</p>
<ul>
<li>Recruiter screen</li>
<li>Hiring manager interview</li>
<li>60-min mock call</li>
<li>Panel</li>
<li>VP</li>
<li>Closing</li>
</ul>
<p>…is NOT standard for roles under $150k.</p>
<p>It means:</p>
<ul>
<li>High turnover</li>
<li>Immature team</li>
<li>They don’t know what they want</li>
<li>They are compensating with more interviews</li>
<li>They are scared of risk</li>
</ul>
<p>Not you.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ The bottom line</h1>
<p>You're not crazy.<br>
You’re not alone.<br>
Companies ARE making it harder, and it IS stupid.</p>
<p>But you’re smart enough to work around it — and I can help you pick the ones worth your time.</p>
<hr>
<p>If you want, I can help you:</p>
<p>✨ Evaluate whether THIS company is worth going through all these steps<br>
✨ Tailor answers for their interview rounds<br>
✨ Prep for the mock call so you pass it easily<br>
✨ Decide whether to move forward or skip it</p>
