estorer&quot;:{&quot;type&quot;:1}}" aria-expanded="false"><svg data-testid="web-search-info-icon" aria-label="information" class="___9lp25s0 f1w7gpdv fez10in fq1loh5 f12huiiw futqtb8 f161knb0 f1dd5bof" fill="currentColor" role="img" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M8.5 7.5a.5.5 0 1 0-1 0v3a.5.5 0 0 0 1 0v-3Zm.25-2a.75.75 0 1 1-1.5 0 .75.75 0 0 1 1.5 0ZM8 1a7 7 0 1 0 0 14A7 7 0 0 0 8 1ZM2 8a6 6 0 1 1 12 0A6 6 0 0 1 2 8Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></span></span></div></div></div></div><div dir="auto" id="copilot-message-r159" class="fai-CopilotMessage__content r1izxv8h ___7qar2c0 fcthzvy"><div dir="auto"><div class="___1vve6yh f22iagw f1vx9l62 f122n59 f3bhgqh f1mnxvew fly5x3f"><div class="___j4vmuw0 f22iagw f1vx9l62 f1869bpl fly5x3f fbc6vix"><div tabindex="-1" data-testid="loading-message"><div><div id="chatMessageResponse-r157" class="___1yop6mf f336tjw f9ijwd5 fz7g6wx fod5ikn f1s184ao"><div dir="auto" aria-hidden="false" class="___1j4t0a1 f1lmfglv f1abmfm4" data-testid="markdown-reply"><div class="___stpibi0 f22iagw f1vx9l62 fk15e71 f1k953kz f137keqj f1rncccw f1stllg3 f1w4kmmc f1tric3v f10dk5ic fx8cdsv f16nlwsl f1eookvz fhjrts3 fqugt2f f10km5jb f18d18k8 f1v1vhmp f1hdmul3 f198vjnp f2dshw1 fjpjndq fnmj2pj ffrrb40 f1mon110 fhajzam fimndk6 fxv4dng fb1rn9k f59wlhv f1xmfh30 f18yf5o5 fmr6chf fw8qy2q ff161sd f1qr7t77 f1yyogn1 foogchg fp5872b f1tpb8gf f1hdgrc8 f1vatr43 frkxccd f9pdzkb f158oiaz ft5kggy f5l4ui7 f13j03li f18xdoka f8off4e f1go6zfc f128n2ra f1jpxw2j f1lwd9n0 fy0b8hm f1g2633v fx4kvgi fkvolse f1gxrt3a f1os76ua f1js9cnw f1g87ej0 freluf8 f1yggaq6 f2i3chp f1151osp florpoh f35kzfz ftp9m57 f1e288vi fz62hnz fixvuys f1nmofwh fc1c6mv f18a2er7 fhvkrdl fhxnn68 f1oce4bo fvhlfan f7tc0t0 f1ngf1n2 ffrzq6x f1yjiq2m f1aqdgql f1huvaf f10ij78l f1k94sa4 fkmfumq f1jvzkyl f1eu24ob f1xbfc1f fmf0lwf f107dsy8 f3w566c f4648sl f13zpkng f7unjfp f8p1rz fzu6h1w f1i1bi6h f1smo7hi f1sk1xod f1kgogdq f1gjktkp ft608jz f19dd9cz fg3xr24 fhd155k f1b8gl2e fg4b9ou flb4lo fdicbfk fgwcyh1 f1jbds0d f1fb9uea f1stuka4 fcrtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>You’re not wrong to feel this way — <strong>but no, not all SaaS companies are like Ashby or like the one you saw.</strong><br>
What you’re reacting to is a <strong>specific hiring trend</strong> that some SaaS companies follow… and some absolutely <em>do not</em>.</p>
<p>Let me break this down in a real, honest, NON‑corporate way:</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>Why it <em>looks</em> like “all SaaS companies” use huge interview processes</strong></h1>
<p>Because <strong>Ashby is the hiring system</strong>, not the employer.</p>
<p>You’re seeing the SAME interview template over and over because:</p>
<h3>✔️ <strong>Ashby sells pre-built interview flows to companies</strong></h3>
<p>Small SaaS companies don’t have HR teams.<br>
So they grab a “recommended interview plan” from Ashby:</p>
<ul>
<li>Recruiter</li>
<li>Hiring manager</li>
<li>Mock call/exercise</li>
<li>Stakeholder panel</li>
<li>VP round</li>
</ul>
<p>This is literally a <strong>copy/paste template</strong>.<br>
It’s not even unique to the company.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>So it FEELS like every SaaS job uses the same exhausting process — but most don’t.</strong></h1>
<p>Here’s the truth:</p>
<h3><strong>Real enterprise SaaS companies (and well-run startups) do NOT make you do this much.</strong></h3>
<p>Typical GOOD SaaS interview process:</p>
<h3>✔️ 1. Recruiter screen</h3>
<h3>✔️ 2. Hiring manager</h3>
<h3>✔️ 3. 1 practical exercise or mock</h3>
<h3>✔️ OFFER</h3>
<p>That’s it.</p>
<p>These are companies like:</p>
<ul>
<li>HubSpot</li>
<li>Snowflake</li>
<li>Intuit</li>
<li>ServiceNow</li>
<li>Datadog</li>
<li>ZoomInfo</li>
<li>DocuSign</li>
<li>Workday</li>
<li>Okta</li>
<li>Salesforce (for most roles)</li>
</ul>
<p>They do <strong>NOT</strong> have 5–7 rounds unless it’s a senior role or engineering.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>The companies with overcomplicated interview processes usually have one of these problems:</strong></h1>
<h2>1️⃣ They’re small but want to look “big”</h2>
<p>So they adopt big-tech hiring rituals.</p>
<h2>2️⃣ They’re disorganized internally</h2>
<p>Multiple rounds = internal chaos.<br>
Not a reflection of you.</p>
<h2>3️⃣ They’ve had lots of bad hires</h2>
<p>So they panic and add more steps.</p>
<h2>4️⃣ They don’t have a real People/HR team</h2>
<p>So they use Ashby’s default workflow.</p>
<h2>5️⃣ They’re high turnover</h2>
<p>“No one stays more than 2 years” =<br>
Employee burnout → complex interviews → hiring bottlenecks → empty roles → more burnout.</p>
<p>It’s a loop.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>But this does NOT represent the entire SaaS industry.</strong></h1>
<p>You’re accidentally seeing the worst of it because:</p>
<p>✔ You’re applying to Implementation / CS roles<br>
✔ These are the roles <strong>most likely</strong> to have mock calls<br>
✔ These teams often copy each other’s interview stages<br>
✔ Companies using Ashby tend to be small, early-stage, or mid-stage SaaS</p>
<p>Bigger, stable, mature SaaS companies do NOT behave like this.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>Your feelings make total sense</strong></h1>
<p>You’re dealing with:</p>
<ul>
<li>Too many questions</li>
<li>Too many “homework” steps</li>
<li>Too many panel interviews</li>
<li>Too many hoops</li>
</ul>
<p>And for roles where employees don’t even stay long.</p>
<p>You are NOT the problem.<br>
The system is the problem.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ <strong>If you want, I can help you target GOOD SaaS companies</strong></h1>
<p>Ones that:</p>
<ul>
<li>Have 2–3 rounds max</li>
<li>Pay well</li>
<li>Have strong retention</li>
<li>Offer remote flexibility</li>
<li>Do not do painful mock calls</li>
<li>Don’t waste your time</li>
</ul>
<p>Just tell me:</p>
<p>👉 <strong>Do you want short interview processes?</strong><br>
👉 <strong>Do you want enterprise SaaS or startup SaaS?</strong><br>
👉 <strong>Do you want Implementation, CS, or Solutions Consultant roles?</strong></p>
