rtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>You’re not alone — <strong>most people don’t know WHERE to apply anymore</strong>, and LinkedIn + Glassdoor are honestly the worst for burnout because:</p>
<ul>
<li>Too many scam postings</li>
<li>Too many ghost companies</li>
<li>Too many repetitive SaaS startups using Ashby</li>
<li>Too many roles with LONG interview processes</li>
<li>Too many fake or already‑filled jobs</li>
</ul>
<p>So let me help you <strong>fix your job search strategy</strong> so you stop wasting time on the SAME type of roles and the SAME type of companies.</p>
<p>I’m going to give you:</p>
<h2>⭐ 1. The best job sites you SHOULD be using</h2>
<h2>⭐ 2. The specific kinds of companies you should target</h2>
<h2>⭐ 3. Roles that match your background</h2>
<h2>⭐ 4. A custom list of companies for you (if you want)</h2>
<p>And I’ll keep it simple.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 1. <strong>Best places to apply (better than LinkedIn + Glassdoor)</strong></h1>
<p>These platforms have REAL jobs, not recycled ones, and MUCH better SaaS companies.</p>
<h3>🔥 <strong>1. Wellfound (AngelList Talent)</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Perfect for tech &amp; SaaS</li>
<li>Shows <em>exact funding stage</em></li>
<li>Lets you filter by “no mock calls,” “no take-home assignment,” etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>👉 https://wellfound.com</p>
<hr>
<h3>🔥 <strong>2. Otta (my #1 recommendation for you)</strong></h3>
<p>Matches roles to your experience, shows company culture + retention, and you can skip the high-chaos companies.</p>
<p>It literally tells you:</p>
<ul>
<li>Fast-growing</li>
<li>Good work-life balance</li>
<li>Low interview rounds</li>
<li>High employee satisfaction</li>
</ul>
<p>👉 https://otta.com</p>
<hr>
<h3>🔥 <strong>3. BuiltIn (for remote SaaS + tech jobs)</strong></h3>
<p>Great for Implementation, CS, and Tech PM roles.</p>
<p>👉 https://builtin.com</p>
<hr>
<h3>🔥 <strong>4. YC Jobs (Y Combinator startups)</strong></h3>
<p>These jobs are REAL and actively hiring.<br>
Also shows pay ranges and remote-first companies.</p>
<p>👉 https://www.ycombinator.com/jobs</p>
<hr>
<h3>🔥 <strong>5. Indeed (but ONLY for hospital → tech crossover roles)</strong></h3>
<p>You will see Implementation roles, Rev Cycle Analytics, EHR Integrations, Revenue Cycle PM roles, etc.</p>
<hr>
<h3>🔥 <strong>6. Company career sites directly</strong></h3>
<p>Because LOTS of roles never make it to job boards.</p>
<p>Some excellent ones for YOUR background:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Intuit</strong></li>
<li><strong>ServiceNow</strong></li>
<li><strong>Workday</strong></li>
<li><strong>Salesforce</strong></li>
<li><strong>Veeva</strong></li>
<li><strong>Epic Systems</strong></li>
<li><strong>CureMD</strong></li>
<li><strong>Health Catalyst</strong></li>
<li><strong>Change Healthcare</strong></li>
<li><strong>R1</strong></li>
<li><strong>Accenture Health</strong></li>
<li><strong>Netsmart</strong> (behavioral health tech)</li>
</ul>
<p>These companies have:
✔ Better pay<br>
✔ Fewer interview steps<br>
✔ Huge implementation teams<br>
✔ Stability<br>
✔ Real training<br>
✔ Remote roles</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 2. Companies YOU should avoid</h1>
<p>You keep applying to mid-stage SaaS doing:</p>
<ul>
<li>Ashby ATS</li>
<li>6 rounds</li>
<li>Mock calls</li>
<li>Panels</li>
<li>Exercises</li>
<li>VP involvement</li>
<li>Early-stage startup chaos</li>
</ul>
<p>THESE are the companies burning you out.</p>
<p>You need to shift to <strong>enterprise SaaS</strong>, not startup SaaS.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 3. Jobs that match your background PERFECTLY</h1>
<p>With your Revenue Integrity + multi-system + audit + charge capture + cross-functional workflow experience, you fit into:</p>
<h3>✔ Implementation Specialist</h3>
<h3>✔ Technical Implementation Consultant</h3>
<h3>✔ Solutions Consultant</h3>
<h3>✔ Customer Success Engineer</h3>
<h3>✔ Rev Cycle Analyst → Tech Client Services</h3>
<h3>✔ EMR/EHR Implementation Analyst</h3>
<h3>✔ SaaS Onboarding Specialist</h3>
<h3>✔ Data Implementation Analyst</h3>
<h3>✔ Healthcare Integrations Analyst</h3>
<h3>✔ Business Systems Analyst</h3>
<h3>✔ Clinical/Financial Systems Analyst</h3>
<p>All of those pay:
💰 <strong>$85k–$145k</strong><br>
💰 Full remote<br>
💰 Better stability<br>
💰 Less chaos than startups</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 4. If you want, I can build you a custom list</h1>
<p>If you tell me:</p>
<ul>
<li>Salary target</li>
<li>Remote only?</li>
<li>Healthcare tech vs general SaaS?</li>
<li>Whether you prefer fewer interview rounds</li>
<li>Whether you want enterprise OR early-stage OR mid-stage companies</li>
</ul>
<p>I can give you:</p>
<p>🔥 <strong>A curated list of 20–40 companies that fit EXACTLY what you want</strong><br>
🔥 With roles you can apply to TODAY<br>
🔥 With the interview complexity labeled<br>
🔥 With salary ranges<br>
🔥 With hiring deadlines<br>
🔥 With your résumé tailored to them</p>
<hr>
<h1>💬 You said: “idk where to apply”</h1>
<p>Let me fix that for you.</p>
<p>Just answer these 3 questions:</p>
<h3>1. Do you want <strong>remote only</strong> or hybrid is okay?</h3>
<h3>2. Do you prefer <strong>healthcare SaaS</strong>, or are you open to ANY SaaS?</h3>
<h3>3. What’s your <strong>minimum salary</strong> (realistic target is $95k–$115k+ for you)?</h3>
<p>After that, I’ll build your personalized list.</p>
