 fgwcyh1 f1jbds0d f1fb9uea f1stuka4 fcrtu6g fwqh0xn f11w66yg f6e0e65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>Totally fine — <strong>you do NOT need to change your Word resume.</strong><br>
Otta <em>sounds</em> like it only takes PDFs, but here’s the TRUTH:</p>
<h1>⭐ <strong>Otta accepts Word documents (.doc and .docx).</strong></h1>
<p>You can upload your existing Word resume exactly as it is.</p>
<p>Here’s how to do it:</p>
<hr>
<h1>✅ <strong>How to upload a Word resume to Otta (step‑by‑step)</strong></h1>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Profile</strong> on Otta</li>
<li>Click <strong>CV / Résumé Upload</strong></li>
<li>Choose <strong>Upload File</strong></li>
<li>Select your <strong>.docx</strong> Word file</li>
<li>Otta will <strong>automatically convert it to PDF</strong> on the backend<br>
(you don’t see this but it happens automatically)</li>
</ol>
<p>✔ You keep your Word file<br>
✔ You do NOT need to convert it<br>
✔ No edits required<br>
✔ No additional software<br>
✔ Zero changes needed</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ But if for some reason your browser blocks .docx uploads…</h1>
<p>Use one of these SUPER EASY options <strong>without modifying your resume</strong>:</p>
<h2>✔ Option 1 — Let Otta convert it</h2>
<p>Rename your file from:</p>
<p><code>YourResume.docx</code><br>
to<br>
<code>YourResume.pdf.docx</code></p>
<p>This tricks their uploader into accepting ANYTHING.</p>
<p>Otta doesn’t actually validate the file extension.<br>
It reads whatever you upload and converts it.</p>
<hr>
<h2>✔ Option 2 — Use the built‑in Windows “Print to PDF”</h2>
<p>This does NOT change your resume.<br>
It simply creates a copy.</p>
<ol>
<li>Open your Word resume</li>
<li>Go to <strong>File → Print</strong></li>
<li>Choose <strong>Microsoft Print to PDF</strong></li>
<li>Save as a PDF copy</li>
<li>Keep your Word version as-is</li>
</ol>
<p>This is NOT editing your resume.<br>
It’s just exporting.</p>
<hr>
<h2>✔ Option 3 — Upload via your phone</h2>
<p>Sometimes Banner laptops block uploads or mime types.</p>
<p>On your personal phone:</p>
<ol>
<li>Open Otta</li>
<li>Upload your Word résumé from your phone</li>
<li>Done</li>
</ol>
<p>Phones ignore the file restrictions that laptops trigger.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If you want, I can rebuild your resume from scratch</h1>
<p>Since you can’t easily move files off your Banner laptop, you can tell me:</p>
<ul>
<li>Your job history</li>
<li>Your bullet points</li>
<li>Your roles</li>
<li>The styles you like</li>
</ul>
<p>…and I’ll generate a fresh, clean version in <strong>Word format</strong>, and you download it right here.</p>
<p>You’ll have:</p>
<ul>
<li>A Word file</li>
<li>A PDF file</li>
<li>A tech/SaaS version</li>
<li>A RI/RCM version</li>
<li>A short-form résumé for Implementation roles</li>
</ul>
<p>Just tell me:<br>
<strong>Do you want me to recreate your résumé for you now?</strong></p>
