65 f1vvgu0 f1607507 f1m9bycv f1ntoah8 f1b694rt faql4r2 fpjuhzh fmavl6h"><p>Got you — and THANK YOU for being patient.<br>
Let’s fix this <strong>cleanly and quickly</strong> so you can use Otta without changing your existing Word resume.</p>
<p>You said:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>“Its file must be PDF”</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>So here are the ONLY <strong>safe, fast, guaranteed</strong> ways to convert your Word resume into PDF <strong>WITHOUT editing it</strong>, <strong>WITHOUT reformatting</strong>, and <strong>WITHOUT violating Banner policies.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ OPTION 1 — Convert to PDF <strong>ON YOUR BANNER LAPTOP</strong> (No Email Needed)</h1>
<p>This does <strong>not</strong> modify your Word file.<br>
It simply creates a <strong>separate PDF copy</strong>.</p>
<h3>✔ Windows “Print to PDF” (FASTEST)</h3>
<ol>
<li>Open your Word resume on the Banner laptop</li>
<li>Click <strong>File → Print</strong></li>
<li>Under Printer, select:<br>
<strong>Microsoft Print to PDF</strong></li>
<li>Click <strong>Print</strong></li>
<li>It will ask “Save As” → choose Desktop</li>
<li>Name it something like:<br>
<code>Resume_Leovie.pdf</code></li>
</ol>
<p>Done.</p>
<p>You now have a PDF file <strong>without changing anything</strong> in your original Word document.</p>
<p><strong>Banner does NOT block this.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ OPTION 2 — Convert Using Word “Save As PDF” (Also Safe)</h1>
<ol>
<li>Open the resume in Word</li>
<li>File → Save As</li>
<li>Choose location (Desktop)</li>
<li>Under file type, select:<br>
<strong>PDF (.pdf)</strong></li>
<li>Save</li>
</ol>
<p>This is just exporting — not editing.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ OPTION 3 — Upload the Word file to any job portal that accepts Word → auto-convert → download PDF on personal device</h1>
<p>Since Banner allows uploads to job sites:</p>
<p>Upload your Word resume to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Indeed</li>
<li>ZipRecruiter</li>
<li>LinkedIn</li>
<li>Glassdoor</li>
<li>ANY application that accepts Word (.doc or .docx)</li>
</ul>
<p>These platforms automatically convert it to PDF.</p>
<p>Then:</p>
<ol>
<li>Log in from your phone or personal laptop</li>
<li>Go to your “resumé on file”</li>
<li>Download the <strong>PDF</strong> version</li>
<li>Use that PDF for Otta</li>
</ol>
<p>This works perfectly if you're unable to export on your Banner laptop.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ OPTION 4 — If you want, I will recreate your resume here <strong>as a PDF</strong></h1>
<p>If you want to skip ALL of that, just say:</p>
<p>👉 <strong>“Yes, convert my resume to PDF.”</strong></p>
<p>Then:</p>
<ol>
<li>You paste your Word resume text here</li>
<li>I recreate it cleanly</li>
<li>I generate a <strong>PDF file</strong></li>
<li>You download it directly to your personal device</li>
<li>Upload to Otta</li>
</ol>
<p>No Banner system involved at all.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ Which option do you want?</h1>
<p>Tell me:</p>
<h3>1. Do you want to convert it yourself using Print to PDF?</h3>
<h3>2. Or do you want me to recreate your PDF resume here so you can download it?</h3>
<p>Either way — we’ll get you a clean PDF fast so you can apply.</p>
