sage-r1b5-title user-message-r1b5" data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="fai-UserMessage rucmimq ___rxrhmb0 fjuset5 f1s184ao fkfq4zb f10kwr27 fmuwq92 f1hyfdyu fjksvth fpgzoln fibxuh5 f6dzj5z"><h5 id="user-message-r1b5-title" class="fai-UserMessage__accessibleHeading r183b29h">You said: </h5><button aria-label="More actions" tabindex="-1" class="fai-UserMessage__actionBarAccessibleButton rb330c"></button><div id="user-message-r1b5" class="fai-UserMessage__message rulz4bx"><div dir="auto" data-testid="chatOutput" class="">As an Application Trainer, you will play a key role in supporting new and existing Bold Group customers as they learn to use our software. You'll deliver engaging training sessions focused on system setup, day-to-day operations, and best practices. Your responsibilities include guiding customers through standard training programs, leading admin and end-user sessions, assisting with data validation walkthroughs, and helping ensure a smooth onboarding experience. You’ll work closely with internal teams to align training content with project milestones and customer needs.

The Application Trainer is responsible for delivering engaging, effective training to new and existing customers using our alarm monitoring and business management software. This role supports successful onboarding and product adoption by providing clear instruction, user-focused learning experiences, and essential product knowledge across our suite of solutions.

Responsibilities:

Deliver high-level application training to business management customers, virtual or in-person.

Lead customer training engagements, onboarding new clients on core software functionality to support successful implementation.

Deliver the full training portfolio, including system setup, administration, application usage, add-on modules, and integrations.

Assess customers’ existing business processes and workflows and provide guidance on effectively transitioning those processes from legacy systems into Bold Group solutions.

Consult with customers to identify implementation use cases, user roles, workflows, and application requirements.

Partner with the Learning &amp; Development team to develop, maintain, and manage client-facing training materials, including documentation, agendas, audit checklists, and training resources.

Advise customers on process improvements and best practices to maximize product adoption, utilization, and overall satisfaction with Bold Group solutions.

Collaborate with Customer Success to deliver in-application training and solutions for at-risk customers, helping to reduce churn and improve retention.

Work closely with technical consultants during data conversion and implementation phases to guide data structure, reporting, and configuration best practices.

Support customer re-engagement initiatives, including identifying add-on, cross-sell, and upsell opportunities, to enhance customer experience and product value.

Serve as a subject matter expert (SME) for Bold Group applications by supporting Sales and Marketing teams as needed.

Contribute to industry-facing content, including webinars, white papers, case studies, blogs, and other thought leadership materials.

Develop and document application best practices with a focus on user experience and usability.

Maintain up-to-date knowledge of Bold Group products, technologies, and industry trends through continuous learning.

Represent Bold Group at trade shows, conferences, and customer events, supporting sales efforts as an application SME, as needed.

Participate in internal product testing and validation efforts as an application subject matter expert, as needed.

Travel up to 10% to customer sites, conferences, or trade shows as required.

Skills and Experience needed for success in this role:

5+ years of experience in software application consulting, software training, professional services, product-focused sales, or a related customer-facing role.

Strong understanding of security industry best practices or the ability to quickly develop industry expertise.

Proven experience delivering customer-facing software application training.

Ability to clearly and effectively communicate complex technical concepts to users with varying levels of technical knowledge.

Excellent communication, presentation, and influencing skills, including interaction with technical teams, business stakeholders, and executive leadership.

Ability to translate business requirements into practical technical solutions.

Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to systematically investigate issues and propose effective solutions.

Exceptional organizational and time management skills.

Highly self-motivated, results-driven, and comfortable working independently.

Customer-focused mindset with a strong desire to exceed expectations.

Experience in a technical role within the alarm monitoring or business management software industry.

Familiarity with Bold Group business management systems such as Managely, SedonaOffice, or AlarmBiller.

Hands-on experience with ERP implementations, including system configuration, installation, Go-Live support, and a working knowledge of accounting processes.

Ability to travel within the U.S. and Canada.

Where: [REMOTE / U.S. up to 10% travel] 


The EverCommerce team is distributed globally, with teams in the U.S., Canada, the U.K., Jordan, New Zealand, and Australia. With a widely distributed team, we are used to working remotely across different time zones. This role can be based anywhere in the United States– if you’re close to one of our offices, we can set you up in-office or you can work 100% remotely. Please note that you must be eligible to work without sponsorship to qualify for this position, and this role may require travel to our Corporate Headquarters in Denver, Colorado, or to other office locations around North America.

Benefits and Perks:

Flexibility to work where/how you want within your country of employment – in-office, remote, or hybrid

Day 1 access to a robust health and wellness benefits package, including an annual wellness stipend.

401k with up to a 4% match and immediate vesting

Flexible and generous (FTO) time-off

Employee Stock Purchase Program

Compensation: The target base compensation for this position is $70,000-85,000 USD per year in most US locations. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors including location, local market variances, and candidate experience and expertise, and may vary from the amounts listed above.

EverCommerce is an equal opportunity employer and we value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We look forward to reviewing your credentials and getting to know more about your experience!</div></div></div><i tabindex="0" role="none" data-tabster-dummy="" aria-hidden="true" style="position: fixed; height: 1px; width: 1px; opacity: 0.001; z-index: -1; content-visibility: hidden; top: 0px; left: 0px;"></i></div></div><div class="___1mi8yjl f22iagw fz7g6wx"><div class="___kgn7g00 f22iagw f1vx9l62 fpgzoln fh8aql4 f1wvei1u f6c99af fz7g6wx fly5x3f" data-testid="copilot-message-div"><div class="___19ip04d f1s184ao f6c99af" role="" tabindex="-1" dir="auto" data-testid="copilot-message-reply-div"><i tabindex="0" role="none" data-tabster-dummy="" aria-hidden="true" style="position: fixed; height: 1px; width: 1px; opacity: 0.001; z-index: -1; content-visibility: hidden; top: 0px; left: 0px;"></i><div role="article" tabindex="0" aria-labelledby="copilot-message-r1b9-title copilot-message-r1b9" data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" aria-busy="true" name="[object Object]" class="fai-CopilotMessage r1f6yzd6 ___1fjo9g7 f1g2tzg5 fgct6un fy77jfu f2c7lf3"><div class="r17kselw"><h6 id="copilot-message-r1b9-title" class="fai-CopilotMessage__accessibleHeading rhgro0h">Copilot said: </h6><div class="fai-CopilotMessage__avatar rfv3lde"><div><div class="___13m8sud fq4mcun frvgh55 f1uopt3v fnmerfl" data-testid="messageAttributionIcon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-label="Copilot&#39;s Logo" role="img"><path d="M4.69405 17.2446C5.24991 17.2627 5.50461 17.4556 5.6798 17.688C5.91739 18.0031 6.0556 18.4507 6.24191 19.0835L6.25254 19.1196C6.41716 19.6792 6.63012 20.4032 7.07658 20.9706C7.58358 21.615 8.33343 22.00