<p>This Application Trainer role is <strong>VERY close</strong> to an Implementation Specialist / Customer Success implementation role — just heavier on <strong>training</strong>, <strong>workflow teaching</strong>, and <strong>consulting</strong>.</p>
<p>Let me break it down FAST so you can decide.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ SHOULD YOU APPLY?</h1>
<p><strong>YES — you are a strong match for this job.</strong></p>
<p>Here’s why:</p>
<h3>✔ You already train people (informally) every day</h3>
<p>You:</p>
<ul>
<li>Explain Cloudmed findings</li>
<li>Walk Coding/Charge Integrity through corrections</li>
<li>Create job aids and notes</li>
<li>Break down workflows</li>
<li>Communicate complex rev‑cycle rules to non‑tech staff</li>
</ul>
<p>That is exactly what a software trainer does (just different content).</p>
<hr>
<h3>✔ You have healthcare systems experience</h3>
<p>This job requires:</p>
<ul>
<li>SaaS training</li>
<li>Healthcare/lifescience system familiarity</li>
<li>Comfort explaining workflows</li>
</ul>
<p>You’ve worked in:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cloudmed</li>
<li>FinThrive</li>
<li>Lawson</li>
<li>Spacetrax</li>
<li>MS4</li>
<li>Cerner</li>
<li>Craneware</li>
</ul>
<p>These are MUCH harder systems than Bold Group’s software.</p>
<hr>
<h3>✔ You have Implementation-adjacent skills</h3>
<p>They want someone who can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Teach workflows</li>
<li>Guide users during onboarding</li>
<li>Host sessions</li>
<li>Align with project milestones</li>
<li>Translate business processes</li>
<li>Support data validation</li>
</ul>
<p>This is the same as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reviewing audit logic</li>
<li>Explaining charging rules</li>
<li>Fixing workflow gaps</li>
<li>Mapping supply → CDM → claims</li>
<li>Coordinating across teams</li>
</ul>
<p>You’re doing this every day.</p>
<hr>
<h3>✔ Salary: $70k–$85k</h3>
<p>This is <strong>higher</strong> than the EverHealth Implementation Specialist job ($55k–$65k).</p>
<p>And closer to where you want to be.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ WHAT YOU <em>DON’T</em> HAVE (BUT IT DOESN’T MATTER MUCH)</h1>
<h3>❌ Security industry knowledge</h3>
<p>They know 99% of applicants don’t come from alarm/security systems.<br>
They say <em>“or ability to quickly learn”</em> — they expect people to come from other SaaS or healthcare tech backgrounds.</p>
<h3>❌ 5+ years of software training</h3>
<p>You have:</p>
<ul>
<li>5+ years in revenue cycle</li>
<li>5+ years teaching workflows</li>
<li>5+ years explaining complex systems</li>
</ul>
<p>This counts.</p>
<h3>❌ Experience with their tools</h3>
<p>They know this — that’s why training is part of onboarding.</p>
<p>The transferable skills matter more.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ BIG QUESTION: CAN YOU DO THIS JOB?</h1>
<p>Yes.</p>
<p>It’s literally:</p>
<ul>
<li>Hosting group Zoom trainings</li>
<li>Walking customers through setup</li>
<li>Teaching users how to do things</li>
<li>Answering questions</li>
<li>Helping them use the system</li>
<li>Observing workflows</li>
<li>Advising on best practices</li>
<li>Supporting implementation milestones</li>
</ul>
<p>You're already doing that, just internally.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ BIGGER QUESTION: WOULD YOU <em>LIKE</em> this job?</h1>
<p>This depends on you:</p>
<h3>You would like this job if you prefer:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Teaching</li>
<li>Structure</li>
<li>Predictability</li>
<li>Work that feels helpful</li>
<li>Less technical stress</li>
<li>No coding</li>
<li>No deep PM responsibilities</li>
<li>Less intense system troubleshooting</li>
</ul>
<h3>You would <em>not</em> like it if you dislike:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Repeating the same training multiple times</li>
<li>Talking all day</li>
<li>Leading many Zoom calls</li>
<li>Customer-facing Q&amp;A</li>
<li>Teaching slow learners</li>
</ul>
<p>If you prefer <strong>structured, predictable, low-stress work</strong>, you’ll love it.</p>
<p>If you prefer <strong>building systems or deep analysis</strong>, you may want a more technical implementation role.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION FOR YOU</h1>
<p>Based on EVERYTHING I know about you:</p>
<h3>✔ You want remote</h3>
<p>✔ You want less drama<br>
✔ You want to get out of pure RI<br>
✔ You want a gateway into SaaS<br>
✔ You appreciate structure<br>
✔ You want predictable hours<br>
✔ You have strong teaching/explaining skills<br>
✔ You want to feel useful<br>
✔ You want career growth toward Implementation or Solutions Consultant</p>
<p><strong>This is a GOOD MATCH.</strong></p>
<p>And the pay is better than the other roles you’ve looked at.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ If you want, I can:</h1>
<p>🔥 Write your answers for the application questions<br>
🔥 Tailor your resume to “Application Trainer”<br>
🔥 Write your “Why I’m a fit” paragraph<br>
🔥 Create bullets that highlight training + workflow teaching<br>
🔥 Prepare interview answers</p>
<p>Just tell me what you want me to help with next.</p>
