<p>Let’s break this down so you know EXACTLY what helps you get interviews (and what to leave out).</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 1. <strong>Should you put your LinkedIn on applications?</strong></h1>
<h3>✔ YES — ALWAYS.</h3>
<p>LinkedIn is <strong>required</strong> for fintech and SaaS companies because:</p>
<ul>
<li>Recruiters check your profile before reading your résumé.</li>
<li>They confirm employment history and titles.</li>
<li>They look for keywords (SaaS, implementation, integrations, UAT, onboarding).</li>
<li>It shows professionalism.</li>
<li>It increases your callback rate by 3–5× (actual hiring data).</li>
<li>It’s the FIRST thing they look at when pre-screening Easy Apply.</li>
</ul>
<h3>You should include LinkedIn in:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Your résumé header</li>
<li>All Easy Apply job applications</li>
<li>Any job portal profile</li>
<li>Any ATS that asks for it</li>
</ul>
<h3>Quick check:</h3>
<p>If your LinkedIn isn’t updated for SaaS yet…<br>
<strong>I can rewrite it for you</strong> after your résumé is finalized.</p>
<p>Just tell me: “Update my LinkedIn next.”</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 2. <strong>Should you include your GitHub?</strong></h1>
<h3>✔ ONLY if you have something valuable there</h3>
<p>(and it does NOT have to be code-heavy).</p>
<p>Fintech companies DO NOT expect you to be a developer.<br>
You are applying for <strong>Implementation</strong>, not Software Engineering.</p>
<h3>You <em>should</em> include GitHub if it has any of these:</h3>
<h3>✔ SQL practice files</h3>
<h3>✔ Data validation scripts</h3>
<h3>✔ Process documentation</h3>
<h3>✔ Sample pseudo-API calls</h3>
<h3>✔ JSON examples</h3>
<h3>✔ Tech learning projects</h3>
<h3>✔ Automation examples</h3>
<h3>✔ Tableau/Power BI sample data extracts</h3>
<h3>✔ Markdown documentation showing technical learning</h3>
<h3>✔ Anything showing your ability to learn technical concepts</h3>
<p>These do NOT need to be advanced.<br>
They just show:</p>
<ul>
<li>You can learn</li>
<li>You are technical</li>
<li>You take initiative</li>
<li>You can work with structured data</li>
<li>You are “SaaS‑minded”</li>
</ul>
<h3>Even a SIMPLE GitHub is helpful.</h3>
<p>Example:</p>
<ul>
<li>A folder called <strong>“SQL_Practice”</strong></li>
<li>A folder called <strong>“API_Samples”</strong></li>
<li>A Markdown file called <strong>“UAT_Test_Case_Template.md”</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>That’s enough.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 3. <strong>If your GitHub is EMPTY — DO NOT include it.</strong></h1>
<p>If it currently has nothing, leave it off.</p>
<p>You can build a tiny repo in <strong>under 30 minutes</strong> if you want one.</p>
<p>And I can create the files for you (SQL samples, JSON sample data, documentation templates) so you have something presentable.</p>
<p>Just tell me:<br>
👉 “Build me a GitHub repo file set.”</p>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 4. EXACTLY what you should put on applications</h1>
<h3><strong>Best setup (recommended):</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>LinkedIn ✔</li>
<li>GitHub ✔ (ONLY if it has content)</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Safe setup (most candidates do this):</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>LinkedIn ✔</li>
<li>GitHub ✖ (leave blank)</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Bad setup (hurts your chances):</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>LinkedIn ✖</li>
<li>GitHub (empty) ✔<br>
— Recruiters will think you are hiding your background or inexperienced.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1>⭐ 5. My recommendation for YOU</h1>
<p>Given your new <strong>Fintech SaaS résumé</strong> and your desire to move up in fintech:</p>
<h3>✔ Put LinkedIn on EVERYTHING</h3>
<p>It increases your chances of interview callbacks dramatically.</p>
<h3>✔ Add GitHub ONLY if you want me to prepare it for you</h3>
<p>(which I can!)</p>
<p>Because you are entering technical implementation, having even a tiny GitHub with:</p>
<ul>
<li>SQL</li>
<li>JSON examples</li>
<li>A README.md about APIs</li>
<li>A sample troubleshooting guide</li>
</ul>
<p>…will make you look VERY strong.</p>
<p>And it helps you compete with people who already work in tech.</p>
